  Consistent Faces, Face Swapping, and Restoration

In this video, I'll show you how to get consistent faces from your Midjourney images.

Insight Face Swap (Step-by-Step):

  1. Use the /saveid command to save a new ID. Make sure the image lighting is flat and the subject's face is clearly visible. You can set up to 20 IDs at this point.
  2. Use /setid to set who your face will be swapping with. You can use up to 2 faces at a time.
    1. For multiple people, separate the names with a comma (example: /setid tamara,kim)
  3. Use /listid to see a full list of ID names in your library.
  4. Use /delid to delete an ID from your library.
